  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Engaging and Empowering Rape Victims, Survivors of Assault and other Social and State Actors</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In India, women and girls especially from socially excluded communities face various forms of discrimination and violence including sexual abuse and rape. In the recent years there has been some progressive guidelines and programs introduced by state to deal with the problem. However much remains to be done both at the state level and individual level.  This project focuses on one hand with the survivors for building their capacity to deal with the situation and access justice through the legal procedure. On the other hand, it engages with the service delivery agencies including the police department, health officials, judiciary, legal systems and other grass root level government health workers to ensure efficiency in service delivery with sensitivity and dignity.

For the 2nd year of the project, the partner has incorporated a new component to work towards reeducation in prevalence of caste based commercial sexual exploitation in the state of Madhya Pradesh and Rajasthan. There is little information available on the issue. The CSO proposes an action research which would build the evidence base for advocacy with policy makers and government representatives to ensure livelihood and other entitlements.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will bring significant change in dealing with violence against women with specific focus on women from poor and marginalized communities especially those living in the remote part of the Rajasthan and Madhya Pradesh. They will be empowered to break the silence about rape and sexual assault and access their entitlements and justice through the legal system. A conducive environment created by engaging with family and community members especially men and boys by breaking the myths and gender stereotypes related to women&#x2019;s sexuality that further victimizes women and girls. Various campaign and advocacy initiatives would help in ensuring implementation of various protocols, guidelines prescribed by the government agencies and scrapping off of some inhuman medico-legal practices such as the &#x2018;two-finger test&#x2019;. Initiate advocacy and campaign against the practice of caste based sexual exploitation of women and girls.</narrative>
  </description>
